Input.question1: Who was Joe Biden married to when he was first elected to the Senate?
Answer.Res1: Joe Biden was elected to the Senate from Delaware in 1972, and he assumed office on January 3, 1973. He married Nelia Hunter in 1966, and she died in 1972. Joe Biden married Jill Jacobs in 1977. Therefore, he was unmarried when he was first elected to the Senate.
